western clothes, young people in Morocco don’t know their culture, Ethiopian women do this and that. Well, how embarrassing you do this and that? What is it with people that whenever produce something new, they complain and hate on it? Do we really as Africans have no refreshing ideas of our own? Kpate, Malian Fashion line in Bamako does, Aylla a savannah fashion brand in Ethiopia, Nerdani fashion studio in Zimbabwe, Naledi Johannesburg, Yebua Santaram in Tanzania, Stylafly in Kenya, 1330 Fashion and Suka Tanzania in Tanzania. These companies aren’t all perfect, and I am not calling out Chaka. Let’s support these new wave of eCommerce businesses, market their products, and let’s not be biased.

A friend and client of mine, Dozie Wokes, a content creator was asked to do a content series for a branding and marketing consultancy that repped well known brands and big clients, including the competition. He did a series. Three months later, they responded to say it wasn’t a good fit, thank you, bye bye. A month later the brand they repped released the content on their Instagram page without identifying the photographer. By any means am I asking people to copy her shoot or her content, but it’s important that we support each other and remove this jealousy/fake perception of competition. Ultimate digital entrepreneurship success.
